               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-373" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-373" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-373" type="surname" value="GRACE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-373" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD GRACE</persName>
                  </hi>. This property belonged to Henry Grace, and another,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183709180045"></xptr>
               <p>the partner, colour merchants, in Old-street. The prisoner had worked in his manufactory three or four years as a labourer and porter—I am in their employ—having some suspicion, on the 1st of September, as the prisoner was leaving work, when he had passed the counting-house door going out, I called him into the counting-house, and took off his hat, and found the Prussian blue in his hat—he said, he did not know how it came there, or what it was—he thought it was good for nothing—it is worth about five shillings.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> You cannot swear it was their property? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, I can—he had taken a great deal, I dare say—his hat was stained with Prussian blue—he had seventeen shillings a week, I think.</p>
               <p>
